{{Infobox journal | title = Angelaki: Journal of the Theoretical Humanities | cover = | caption = | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = Angelaki | discipline = [[Humanities]], including: [[Continental Philosophy]], [[Literary Theory]], [[Cultural Theory]], Art Theory, [[Social Theory]], [[Political Theory]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English | editor = Lead editors: Charlie Blake (Theme Commissioning Editor), Pelagia Goulimari (General Editor), Gerard Greenway (Editor), Salah el Moncef bin Khalifa (General Issue Editor) | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = [[United Kingdom]] | history = 1993 to present | frequency = Six issues per year: four theme issues, two 'general' (nontheme) issues | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 0969-725X | eISSN = 1469-2899 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/cang20 | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }}
'''''Angelaki: Journal of the Theoretical Humanities''''' is a British-based international [[academic journal]] founded in 1993 that "represents the productive nexus of work in the disciplinary fields of literary criticism and theory, philosophy, and cultural studies."<ref>{{cite web|title=Angelaki: journal of the theoretical humanities|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=aimsScope&journalCode=cang20}}</ref> Since 1998, it has been published by [[Routledge]], an imprint of the [[Taylor & Francis Group]]. In 1996, while it was still an independent publication, the journal was named "Best New Journal" in the annual awards of the [[Council of Editors of Learned Journals]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CELJ Winners |url=https://thecouncilofeditorsoflearnedjournals.wildapricot.org/winners}}</ref> The journal is [[abstracting and indexing|abstracted and indexed]] in [[Scopus]],<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |title=Content overview |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus |accessdate=2016-03-10}}</ref> [[Current Contents]]/Arts & Humanities, and [[Arts and Humanities Citation Index]],<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2016-03-10}}</ref> amongst others.<ref>{{cite web|title=Journal Information, Angelaki|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?journalCode=cang20}}</ref>
From 1993 until 2010 the journal published three issues a year. This was increased to four issues a year in 2011. In 2018, the journal's 25th-anniversary year, the frequency was further increased to six issues per volume, a volume normally comprising four special issues and two general (nontheme) issues.<ref>{{cite web|title=Journal Information, Angelaki|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?journalCode=cang20}}</ref> Special issues of the journal are frequently republished by Routledge as books. In 1996 editors of the journal established an associated book series, Angelaki Humanities, with Manchester University Press.
