{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Sport and Tourism |nativename = <small>Ministerstwo Sportu i Turystyki</small> |logo = Logo msit RP.jpg |logo_width = 200px |logo_caption = Ministerial logotype |seal = Polish Governmental and Diplomatic Plaque.svg |seal_width = 150px |seal_caption = Official governmental wall plaque |formed = |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = ul. Senatorska 14, [[Warsaw]] |employees = |budget = |chief1_name = [[Witold Bańka]] |chief1_position = Minister of Sport and Tourism |chief2_name = |chief2_position = First Deputy Minister |parent_agency = [[Council of Ministers of the Republic of Poland|Council of Ministers]] |website = [http://www.msport.gov.pl/ www.msport.gov.pl] |footnotes = }}
[[Image:Pałac Blanka.jpg|thumb|250px|right|The seat of the Ministry of Sport and Tourism is today the Blanka Palace in Central [[Warsaw]]]]
'''Ministry of Sport and Tourism of the [[Republic of Poland]]''' was created on {{dts|2005|8|23}} by decision of the Council of Ministers under then-[[Prime Minister of Poland|Prime Minister]] [[Marek Belka]].
It was renamed on {{dts|2007|7|23}} when tourism was placed under ministry authority.
Ministry goals: * Overseeing sport clubs * Matters related to sport * Matters related to tourism
State-controlled ''Polska Konfederacja Sportu'' (Polish Sport Union) became integral part of the ministry.
