{{taoism}} {{Unreferenced|date=July 2010}}
'''''Qīngtán''''' ({{zh|t=清談|w=Ch'ing<sup>1</sup>-t'an<sup>2</sup>|l=pure conversation}}) was a movement related to [[Taoism]] that developed during the [[Cao Wei|Wei]]-[[Jin Dynasty (265–420)|Jin]] ({{lang|zh|魏晉}}) period and continued on through the [[Southern and Northern dynasties]]. Qingtan involved witty conversation or debates about [[metaphysics]] and [[philosophy]].
== See also == * [[Xuanxue]]
== External links == * [http://digitalcommons.libraries.columbia.edu/dissertations/AAI9202757/ The voices of Wei-Jin scholars: A study of 'qingtan']{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} * [http://www.britannica.com/eb/topic-112975/qingtan Qingtan, or ch’ing-t’an, or pure conversation], (Chinese philosophy in Encyclopædia Britannica). * [https://books.google.com/books?id=I14u8_uRi00C&pg=PA551&lpg=PA551&dq=%22reine+gespr%C3%A4ch%22+qingtan&source=web&ots=W7B8Nnn0EX&sig=ZPC8JPHehLpCpnAqNziee3zyY2A&hl=de#PPA551,M1 Vom traditionellen China zum modernen Taiwan] (German) * [https://web.archive.org/web/20110716055148/http://www.sphinx-suche.de/weisheitslehren1/chingtan.htm Ch'ing-t’an] (German)
